1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:02,210
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,210 --> 00:00:03,910
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:07,810
He said I looked familiar, too.

4
00:00:08,650 --> 00:00:09,710
No way...

5
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:12,720
Pork cutlet is my absolute favorite.
You look strangely familiar.

6
00:00:16,620 --> 00:00:17,620
Yang Hyun Bin.

7
00:00:27,930 --> 00:00:29,000
Jun Hyeok, where are you?

8
00:00:29,130 --> 00:00:33,340
Where's a guy with no girlfriend
or plans on a weekend?

9
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:35,940
- At work?
- Yes, what's up?

10
00:00:36,470 --> 00:00:39,740
- You know someone in HR, right?
- Yes, what's up?

11
00:00:40,350 --> 00:00:43,250
No questions asked,
just get me the director's name.

12
00:00:43,450 --> 00:00:46,750
- That would be Pacundo...
- Not that one. His Korean name.

13
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:49,420
(Episode 5)

14
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:54,790
- One pork cutlet, please.
- Okay.

15
00:01:30,430 --> 00:01:31,860
(I could eat this every day!)

16
00:01:31,930 --> 00:01:33,130
(Fell in love with the guy
who works here!)

17
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:34,430
(Opening a new location soon?)

18
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:40,270
(We love the owner, Cutlet King!)

19
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:42,910
Come on.

20
00:01:49,010 --> 00:01:51,650
(Yang Hyun Bin
and Gong Ju Ah were here. )

21
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,350
"Yang Hyun Bin
and Gong Ju Ah were here."

22
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:55,120
This pork cutlet is so good.

23
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:05,460
Crybaby Yang Hyun Bin
is going to study abroad.

24
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:26,150
(Pork cutlet with cheese)

25
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,360
(Great vibe, food, cute owner!)

26
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:58,820
So, what did you find out?
The director's name?

27
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:01,290
He wasn't imitating Hyun Bin
for no reason.

28
00:03:01,290 --> 00:03:03,090
His name is Hyun Bin. Yang Hyun Bin.

29
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:06,890
Got it. See you later.

30
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,330
- One pork cutlet, please.
- You got it.

31
00:03:38,090 --> 00:03:39,090
Liar.

32
00:03:40,060 --> 00:03:41,660
As if you were going to remember
anyway.

33
00:03:50,130 --> 00:03:51,140
Thank you.

34
00:03:51,970 --> 00:03:54,210
- Can I get some water, please?
- Yes.

35
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:14,290
Ms. Gong Ju Ah.

36
00:04:15,060 --> 00:04:16,160
Yes, Director.

37
00:04:17,630 --> 00:04:18,830
What are you doing here?

38
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:21,430
I live nearby.

39
00:04:23,130 --> 00:04:25,500
That's right. You do.

40
00:04:25,970 --> 00:04:28,540
What about you, Director?
What brings you here?

41
00:04:29,070 --> 00:04:31,140
Oh, well...

42
00:04:32,010 --> 00:04:33,380
It's just that...

43
00:04:34,950 --> 00:04:36,250
Let me guess.

44
00:04:36,950 --> 00:04:38,820
You were visiting your family.

45
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:40,990
You like checking out restaurants,
and you love pork cutlets,

46
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:42,850
so you must've looked it up.

47
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:46,360
In Onjeong, this is
the most famous pork cutlet spot.

48
00:04:47,130 --> 00:04:48,490
That's why you're here.

49
00:04:49,030 --> 00:04:50,030
Am I right?

50
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:51,630
That's right.

51
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:54,300
You've got it all figured out.

52
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:11,720
Actually,
it's been a while for me, too.

53
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:15,790
I never expected
to run into you here.

54
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,320
Me neither.

55
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:27,370
Remember how I told you
about someone I used to know?

56
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:30,740
A guy named Yang Hyun Bin?

57
00:05:33,540 --> 00:05:35,170
My gosh, here.

58
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,510
Did you?

59
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:41,580
Yes. I mentioned it
at the last company dinner,

60
00:05:42,010 --> 00:05:46,080
and you asked if that Yang Hyun Bin
was my first love, remember?

61
00:05:48,450 --> 00:05:51,020
Right, you said your families
were mortal enemies.

62
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:52,560
Yes.

63
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:55,460
I used to come here
with him sometimes.

64
00:05:58,160 --> 00:05:59,160
I see.

65
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:13,440
I thought I'd be eating alone.
Thanks for keeping me company.

66
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,510
I was just about to say
the same thing.

67
00:06:20,820 --> 00:06:23,520
If you're visiting family,
why did you have lunch alone?

68
00:06:26,020 --> 00:06:27,790
Everyone's just a bit busy.

69
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:30,130
I see.

70
00:06:30,860 --> 00:06:33,260
So are you staying
at your parents' tonight?

71
00:06:33,970 --> 00:06:36,400
No, I'm just planning to head back.

72
00:06:37,740 --> 00:06:39,900
You should at least have dinner
with your family.

73
00:06:41,140 --> 00:06:44,040
You said it's awkward with them.
This is a good chance to get closer.

74
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,680
I've overstepped, haven't I?

75
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:55,150
Seeing you here in the neighborhood,
it felt casual, so I overstepped.

76
00:06:56,220 --> 00:06:57,260
I'm sorry.

77
00:06:59,460 --> 00:07:00,460
Actually...

78
00:07:01,130 --> 00:07:04,100
I'm only here for one year,
and then I go back to Argentina.

79
00:07:08,530 --> 00:07:09,570
I see.

80
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,240
Still, for the year that I'm here,

81
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:14,910
I'll try to get closer
with my family.

82
00:07:17,210 --> 00:07:18,210
All right.

83
00:07:20,910 --> 00:07:23,050
I should get going.

84
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:26,020
- Okay, see you at work.
- Okay.

85
00:07:33,290 --> 00:07:36,760
So, Yang Hyun Bin,
your rival family's son,

86
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:38,130
is Director Pacu Nacho?

87
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:43,030
Yes. And get this.

88
00:07:43,030 --> 00:07:45,140
In the past, he confessed
he had a crush on me.

89
00:07:49,310 --> 00:07:50,340
Wait, but...

90
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:53,180
You figured this out just now?

91
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,510
You didn't recognize him
this whole time?

92
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:58,320
That's right. His personality
and looks have changed so much,

93
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,020
it never even crossed my mind.

94
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:05,290
Then why didn't he let on
that he knew you?

95
00:08:05,490 --> 00:08:06,960
You think
he didn't recognize you either?

96
00:08:07,060 --> 00:08:09,460
No way.
It's not like my name is common.

97
00:08:09,790 --> 00:08:12,260
Plus, he knew where I live.

98
00:08:13,030 --> 00:08:15,170
That's so weird.
Why would he do that?

99
00:08:15,530 --> 00:08:17,500
Maybe he doesn't want
to bring up the past?

100
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:19,440
Anyway, he was...

101
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:24,180
panicking that I'd figured it out.
He was stammering like crazy.

102
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:29,080
My gosh. It was so hard
to pretend I had no idea.

103
00:08:29,780 --> 00:08:32,420
Not at all.
She has absolutely no idea.

104
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:33,890
Are you sure?

105
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:36,250
I'm sure.

106
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:40,320
She probably just thinks that
Yang Hyun Bin and I are a lot alike.

107
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:44,500
Maybe she recognized you
but pretended not to, to spare you.

108
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,360
No.

109
00:08:47,370 --> 00:08:50,170
If she knew, she would have reacted,
knowing Gong Ju Ah.

110
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:55,170
She'd have smacked my head
and yelled, "Crybaby Hyun Bin!"

111
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:57,070
I could have just smacked him
on the back of the head...

112
00:08:57,140 --> 00:09:00,580
and yelled,
"Hey, snot-nosed Yang Hyun Bin!"

113
00:09:00,910 --> 00:09:04,250
Gosh, what a shame, really.
If only he weren't my director.

114
00:09:05,450 --> 00:09:09,750
So you'll just keep treating him
as Director Pacu Nacho from now on?

115
00:09:09,950 --> 00:09:12,990
I have to. He has a girlfriend,

116
00:09:13,060 --> 00:09:16,330
and it would be totally rude
to bring up that first love stuff.

117
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,030
Besides, the director...

118
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:23,370
said he's only staying for one year
before he returns to Argentina.

119
00:09:25,170 --> 00:09:28,340
What's with that look on your face?
You look so disappointed.

120
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:30,640
- I do not.
- Yes, you do. Hey,

121
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:33,810
don't tell me
he was your first love, too.

122
00:09:37,420 --> 00:09:38,980
I really liked her.

123
00:09:39,820 --> 00:09:40,820
Gong Ju Ah...

124
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:43,350
She was my savior,
the one who ended my misery.

125
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,690
I know I was young,

126
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:49,860
but I honestly thought
she was the only one for me.

127
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:53,700
Oh, so that's why you blew me off
when I asked you out.

128
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:56,500
But...

129
00:09:56,970 --> 00:09:59,300
I never contacted her once
after I went to study abroad.

130
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:00,740
Why?

131
00:10:02,170 --> 00:10:05,040
Because we were never meant to be.

132
00:10:05,710 --> 00:10:06,740
What's that supposed to mean?

133
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:09,080
What, are your families
sworn enemies or something?

134
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:11,920
- Yes.
- What?

135
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,680
My grandmother...

136
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:16,250
and Gong Ju Ah's...

137
00:10:18,290 --> 00:10:19,660
grandfather...

138
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:23,960
What? Did they fall in love
and elope or something?

139
00:10:24,730 --> 00:10:26,900
- Yes.
- What?

140
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:31,240
Plus, my dad had a crush
on her mother.

141
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:34,240
He married my mom, not loving her,
and then they got divorced,

142
00:10:34,470 --> 00:10:37,240
and my stepmom knows all about it.

143
00:10:38,010 --> 00:10:39,440
And both our families...

144
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:42,110
are even bigger rivals now
than they were then.

145
00:10:45,180 --> 00:10:46,650
Let me put it this way.

146
00:10:47,850 --> 00:10:50,250
Even now, our grandparents,

147
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:51,890
our parents, their children,
and even our in-laws...

148
00:10:52,090 --> 00:10:55,630
are probably out in the market
fighting each other.

149
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:01,800
- Yang Dong Ik!
- Gong Jeong Han!

150
00:11:01,970 --> 00:11:06,140
- Gong Jeong Han!
- Number two, Gong Jeong Han!

151
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:09,070
- Yang Dong Ik!
- Yang Dong Ik!

152
00:11:09,240 --> 00:11:11,840
- Number 1, Yang Dong Ik!
- Number 1, Yang Dong Ik!

153
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,940
- Yang Dong Ik!
- Louder!

154
00:11:14,010 --> 00:11:16,350
- Yang Dong Ik!
- Yes.

155
00:11:16,410 --> 00:11:18,080
- Number one, Yang Dong Ik!
- Please keep moving.

156
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:21,090
The business expert
of Onjeong Market!

157
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:24,420
I'm Candidate Number One,
Yang Dong Ik!

158
00:11:25,360 --> 00:11:27,930
The trusted doctor of
the Onjeong Market merchants.

159
00:11:28,130 --> 00:11:31,530
I'm Candidate Number Two,
Gong Jeong Han!

160
00:11:31,760 --> 00:11:33,300
(Empathetic Leadership
for the Merchants of Onjeong Market)

161
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,370
(Onjeong Market's Business Expert)

162
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:37,740
Can Onjeong Market
really go on like this?

163
00:11:38,140 --> 00:11:40,170
This market must change!

164
00:11:40,240 --> 00:11:43,170
That's not true, everyone!
The market's traditions...

165
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:45,480
must be preserved!

166
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:48,050
- Gong Jeong Han!
- Yang Dong Ik!

167
00:11:48,310 --> 00:11:49,950
- Yang Dong Ik!
- A candidate who's ready to work.

168
00:11:50,010 --> 00:11:53,550
Empathetic leadership!
Vote for number two, Gong Jeong Han.

169
00:11:53,620 --> 00:11:55,650
- Thank you. Hello there.
- Here.

170
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,120
- Hello.
- A candidate who's ready to work,

171
00:11:57,190 --> 00:12:00,960
Number one, Yang Dong Ik. Thank you.

172
00:12:01,490 --> 00:12:03,960
- Number one, Yang Dong Ik!
- Gong Jeong Han!

173
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:05,030
Hello.

174
00:12:05,030 --> 00:12:09,270
- Number 2, Gong Jeong Han!
- Number 1, Yang Dong Ik!

175
00:12:09,330 --> 00:12:11,840
- Gong Jeong Han! Number two!
- Yang Dong Ik!

176
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:15,310
All right, to all our elders!
If you elect me...

177
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:17,910
Unfair contracts
and rent-fixing schemes.

178
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:21,180
I will personally
put a stop to them!

179
00:12:21,380 --> 00:12:22,980
(Empathetic Leadership
for the Merchants of Onjeong Market)

180
00:12:23,050 --> 00:12:25,550
Hello, young business owners!

181
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:29,350
We'll bring in a youth mall!
We'll build a food court!

182
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:31,620
That is my promise to you!

183
00:12:32,290 --> 00:12:35,960
Are you trying to divide us?
In Candidate Bucket's head,

184
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:38,600
is there no concept
of mutual growth and cooperation?

185
00:12:38,660 --> 00:12:42,700
If we stagnate with no progress
and the market goes under,

186
00:12:42,770 --> 00:12:44,370
are you going to be the one
to take responsibility?

187
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:47,640
What do you mean, "go under?"
It only goes under if you win.

188
00:12:47,710 --> 00:12:49,970
What did you say? You little punk!
Are you done talking?

189
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:53,140
- I'm done. What will you do?
- You jerk! Come here!

190
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:54,880
- This guy, I swear...
- Oh, no!

191
00:12:58,780 --> 00:13:00,650
Why don't you just run your clinic?
You jerk!

192
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,720
- Oh, no. Hey!
- Why, you little...

193
00:13:05,460 --> 00:13:07,120
- All right, both of you...
- Hey!

194
00:13:07,730 --> 00:13:09,230
- Hey!
- That's enough!

195
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,530
- I've had it with this guy.
- Bring it on!

196
00:13:11,530 --> 00:13:13,100
Please, just calm down. Stop!

197
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:15,000
- Let go! Let go of me!
- Hey!

198
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:21,610
- Man, what a day.
- Hello.

199
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:23,110
Hello.

200
00:13:25,780 --> 00:13:27,440
You look exhausted.

201
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,910
Your blood sugar must be low.
Here, have this to recharge.

202
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:31,620
Oh, thank you.

203
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,760
I thought it was your day off,
but you're here.

204
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,890
A good fight is
the best show in town.

205
00:13:40,690 --> 00:13:44,090
You're the one having a tough time,
Officer Jung.

206
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:48,200
Not at all.
I'm having a great time these days.

207
00:13:48,930 --> 00:13:52,900
Compared to my last post, this is...
It's a lot more dynamic.

208
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:54,910
Where were you stationed before?

209
00:13:55,610 --> 00:13:56,610
Jirisan National Park.

210
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:58,240
Wow.

211
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:00,910
- Hello.
- Hello. Yes, vote for number two.

212
00:14:00,910 --> 00:14:02,450
- Hello. Oh, my!
- My gosh.

213
00:14:02,450 --> 00:14:05,320
- Hello.
- Hello.

214
00:14:05,420 --> 00:14:09,950
- You'll vote for number two, right?
- Of course. You've got my support!

215
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:11,020
Yes, I got this.

216
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:15,860
Doctor, you've gotten even prettier
since you were on TV.

217
00:14:15,930 --> 00:14:17,090
Can I get your autograph?

218
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:21,100
Can I get a photo with you?
So I can hang it up in my shop.

219
00:14:22,130 --> 00:14:23,470
- But on one condition...
- Yes?

220
00:14:23,470 --> 00:14:26,440
You must promise to vote for him.
Every vote matters.

221
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:28,010
- My goodness. Of course!
- You got it.

222
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:33,210
- Let's take a picture together.
- All right, picture time!

223
00:14:33,280 --> 00:14:34,910
- Wait, just a second.
- Okay.

224
00:14:35,210 --> 00:14:38,150
Come on, do that thing once for me.
Please?

225
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:41,750
- You know, that thing.
- Go on, do it for them. Yes,

226
00:14:41,820 --> 00:14:43,650
- All right, here we go.
- Just once.

227
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:45,720
- I'm prescribing...
- "I'm prescribing..."

228
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:48,590
- love.
- "love."

229
00:14:48,590 --> 00:14:50,030
I'm really counting
on your support, ma'am.

230
00:14:50,190 --> 00:14:51,430
- Vote for number one.
- One more time.

231
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:55,070
- "I'm prescribing love!"
- I'm prescribing love!

232
00:14:55,130 --> 00:14:58,600
That's great. Oh, my.

233
00:14:58,970 --> 00:15:01,840
- Look at this.
- Oh, you're a good photographer.

234
00:15:01,910 --> 00:15:04,740
Please vote for number 2.
Gong Jeong Han. Number 2!

235
00:15:04,810 --> 00:15:06,310
- Of course.
- Yes, number two.

236
00:15:06,310 --> 00:15:10,750
Hello, everyone. Today at 4 p.m.,

237
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:13,720
come to Onjeong Culture Hall.
The popular trot singer,

238
00:15:13,780 --> 00:15:17,090
- Park Tae Chan, will be performing.
- What?

239
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:18,760
Really? The Park Tae Chan?

240
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:21,760
Wait, Park Tae Chan is coming here?

241
00:15:21,830 --> 00:15:24,160
That's right. Come get an autograph,

242
00:15:24,230 --> 00:15:25,630
and we'll have
tons of free gifts, too.

243
00:15:25,630 --> 00:15:27,600
- Really?
- Wait.

244
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:31,900
We also have a performance at 4 p.m.
at the Merchants' Association Hall.

245
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:33,470
Here, at 4 p.m.?

246
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:35,610
- At 4 p.m.? All right.
- Yes, at 4 p.m.

247
00:15:35,610 --> 00:15:38,510
What performance?
Who do you think you're fooling?

248
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:42,950
If you think I'm bluffing,
come and see for yourself.

249
00:15:43,310 --> 00:15:45,880
- Yes, I'll see you all at 4 p.m.!
- At 4 p.m., yes.

250
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:48,620
- That's right. Thank you.
- At 4 p.m.!

251
00:15:48,690 --> 00:15:50,520
(Onjeong Market Merchants'
Association Presidential Election)

252
00:15:57,460 --> 00:16:02,470
(Featuring Trot King Park Tae Chan!
Onjeong Market's Grand Festival!)

253
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:05,800
What is this?

254
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:09,010
Oh, no!

255
00:16:09,970 --> 00:16:11,580
Yang Dong Suk!

256
00:16:16,550 --> 00:16:17,780
Why are there so few people here?

257
00:16:17,780 --> 00:16:20,520
I was about to ask you that.
What were you doing out there...

258
00:16:20,580 --> 00:16:22,220
that this is the only crowd
you could bring in?

259
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:24,760
I almost forgot
who was running in the election.

260
00:16:24,820 --> 00:16:26,760
Dr. Han's popularity
is through the roof.

261
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:28,630
Everyone's taking pictures with her
and getting autographs.

262
00:16:29,030 --> 00:16:31,430
- Way to read the room.
- What?

263
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:35,700
Where's Father?
He should've come to watch the show.

264
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:38,570
He said he had to prepare herbs,
so he went to the clinic.

265
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,500
Darn it.

266
00:16:40,870 --> 00:16:42,710
I spent a fortune
to get that singer here,

267
00:16:43,170 --> 00:16:44,480
so where did everyone go?

268
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:48,380
They went to the Merchants' Hall.
They have a show there, too.

269
00:16:48,510 --> 00:16:49,510
What?

270
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:53,880
Seriously? They have no money.
What big-shot can they afford?

271
00:16:58,360 --> 00:17:01,590
<i>Here comes Gong Jeong Han</i>

272
00:17:02,060 --> 00:17:05,360
<i>To hold your hand</i>

273
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:09,030
<i>To treat you</i>

274
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:12,600
<i>I'll be the cure you need</i>

275
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:15,540
<i>When the arteries of communication</i>
<i>get clogged</i>

276
00:17:16,310 --> 00:17:19,680
<i>- And you struggle to breathe</i>
<i></i>- Go, Dae Han!

277
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:21,150
<i>- Take a pill of sincerity</i>
<i>- Take a pill of sincerity</i>

278
00:17:21,150 --> 00:17:22,710
<i>- Two pills of empathy</i>
<i>- Two pills of empathy</i>

279
00:17:22,980 --> 00:17:26,450
<i>- And there are no side effects</i>
<i>- And there are no side effects</i>

280
00:17:26,550 --> 00:17:30,020
<i>- Here comes Gong Jeong Han</i>
<i>- Here comes Gong Jeong Han</i>

281
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:33,660
<i>- Onjeong Market's stethoscope</i>
<i></i>- Gong Jeong Han!

282
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:37,090
<i>- Onjeong Market's family doctor</i>
- Gong Jeong Han!

283
00:17:37,090 --> 00:17:40,600
<i>- Onjeong Market's daily vitamin</i>
<i>- Onjeong Market's daily vitamin</i>

284
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:42,570
- Number 2, Gong Jeong Han!
- Number 2, Gong Jeong Han!

285
00:17:43,070 --> 00:17:45,740
<i>Here comes Gong Jeong Han</i>

286
00:17:46,570 --> 00:17:50,370
After this, he's got to win, right?
He just has to.

287
00:17:50,940 --> 00:17:53,680
I said those exact same words
myself once.

288
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:55,780
What do you mean? When was that?

289
00:17:56,450 --> 00:17:57,750
A long time ago.

290
00:17:58,480 --> 00:17:59,820
My kids' father...

291
00:18:00,250 --> 00:18:03,620
was the Merchants' Association
President here once.

292
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:10,990
- This suddenly brings it all back.
<i>- And there are no side effects</i>

293
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:14,770
<i>- Here comes Gong Jeong Han</i>
<i>- Number two!</i>

294
00:18:14,830 --> 00:18:18,340
<i>- Onjeong Market's stethoscope</i>
- Gong Jeong Han!

295
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:21,710
<i>- Onjeong Market's family doctor</i>
- Gong Jeong Han!

296
00:18:21,770 --> 00:18:25,310
<i>Onjeong Market's daily vitamin</i>

297
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:27,280
Thank you!

298
00:18:27,540 --> 00:18:30,180
My gosh.
We just threw our money away.

299
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,920
We hired an expensive singer,
and not even 50 people showed up.

300
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:35,620
Dong Suk. Every single vote counts.

301
00:18:36,050 --> 00:18:38,860
You should've given me the money.
I could've drawn a bigger crowd.

302
00:18:38,860 --> 00:18:39,960
You're back.

303
00:18:42,430 --> 00:18:43,430
Oh, my!

304
00:18:44,460 --> 00:18:48,300
My gosh. Hyun Bin!
When did you get here?

305
00:18:48,370 --> 00:18:49,470
What's all this?

306
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:53,400
I dropped Eun Bin off, so I figured
I'd show off my skills a bit.

307
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:56,870
Hey. You're not like
the men in this family.

308
00:18:56,870 --> 00:18:58,540
Your grandpa and your dad...

309
00:18:58,610 --> 00:19:00,810
act like the world will end
if a man sets foot in the kitchen.

310
00:19:02,210 --> 00:19:04,410
Eun Bin, hurry up and apologize.

311
00:19:05,850 --> 00:19:06,850
Who are you?

312
00:19:07,580 --> 00:19:10,290
What do you mean, who am I?
I'm your daughter!

313
00:19:10,350 --> 00:19:11,420
What daughter?

314
00:19:12,090 --> 00:19:15,090
- You said you weren't my daughter.
- Honey, please.

315
00:19:15,290 --> 00:19:18,230
See?
No one in this family is on my side.

316
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:21,130
Why is Dad yelling at me
when she's the one who messed up?

317
00:19:21,530 --> 00:19:22,570
Hey...

318
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:26,400
Gosh, you can be so harsh.

319
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:27,870
What did you say?

320
00:19:28,510 --> 00:19:29,910
I'll talk to her.

321
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:35,280
Everyone, go wash up and change.
The food's almost ready.

322
00:19:35,480 --> 00:19:37,920
Yes. I should call Grandfather, too.

323
00:19:37,980 --> 00:19:40,320
He has to come try
some of our Hyun Bin's cooking.

324
00:19:40,620 --> 00:19:42,290
Come on, honey. Let's go.

325
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:45,620
Hyun Bin.

326
00:19:46,090 --> 00:19:48,530
You're not sleeping over tonight,
are you?

327
00:19:50,060 --> 00:19:53,660
Auntie, are you worried
I'll say I'm moving back in?

328
00:19:53,730 --> 00:19:54,730
What?

329
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:56,630
Well, yes.

330
00:19:57,430 --> 00:20:01,710
Thanks for being so blunt.
I'm worried I'll get kicked out.

331
00:20:02,140 --> 00:20:04,410
That's not going to happen,
so don't you worry.

332
00:20:04,910 --> 00:20:08,280
I won't be a traditional doctor,
so make sure Ji Hu studies hard,

333
00:20:08,350 --> 00:20:10,050
and make sure
he inherits the clinic.

334
00:20:10,380 --> 00:20:14,620
Wow, my nephew's so direct.
You grew up to be so cool.

335
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:19,390
Gosh, you used to be a mess of tears
when your mom left.

336
00:20:21,190 --> 00:20:22,190
I guess I was.

337
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:24,800
- Thank you.
- Of course.

338
00:20:33,740 --> 00:20:34,910
Ji Hu. Hey, Ji Hu.

339
00:20:36,210 --> 00:20:39,880
Hyun Bin says he has no plans
to take over the clinic.

340
00:20:39,940 --> 00:20:41,550
He told me to make sure
you study hard.

341
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:46,820
Mom, you and Dad both work so hard.
Can't we just move out?

342
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:49,090
We can let Hyun Bin have this room.

343
00:20:49,150 --> 00:20:52,320
Come on, he said
he doesn't want to move in.

344
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:56,230
Besides, we don't have the money.

345
00:20:56,360 --> 00:21:00,600
My income covers our living costs,
and the money your dad earns...

346
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:03,500
We're saving it for your tutoring
and college tuition.

347
00:21:06,570 --> 00:21:09,370
What if Dad wastes it on stocks
or some pyramid scheme again?

348
00:21:10,540 --> 00:21:12,310
You think he wants to get kicked out
by Grandfather?

349
00:21:13,340 --> 00:21:14,340
Don't worry.

350
00:21:14,410 --> 00:21:17,350
I'm keeping an eye on everything
that comes into your dad's account.

351
00:21:22,690 --> 00:21:23,750
Honey!

352
00:21:24,090 --> 00:21:26,690
Hyun Bin has zero intention
of moving in.

353
00:21:26,990 --> 00:21:27,990
Really?

354
00:21:28,460 --> 00:21:30,160
Why are you so nonchalant?

355
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:32,260
You were so worried
we might get kicked out.

356
00:21:33,030 --> 00:21:35,030
- Right.
- Oh, that reminds me.

357
00:21:35,330 --> 00:21:37,100
You have that business trip
next week, don't you?

358
00:21:37,170 --> 00:21:40,700
- Should I pack for you?
- I'll do it. Feed me, I'm starving.

359
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:48,510
This is delicious.

360
00:21:51,150 --> 00:21:52,150
Now, this is what I'm talking about.

361
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:54,520
This is how spicy braised chicken
is supposed to taste.

362
00:21:54,790 --> 00:21:56,620
It's been a while
since I've had it this good.

363
00:21:57,050 --> 00:22:00,060
In the past, it was so bland,

364
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:02,230
I couldn't even tell
what I was eating...

365
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:04,160
Dad.

366
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:08,070
Enjoy.

367
00:22:09,430 --> 00:22:12,740
Let's be honest.
It has been pretty bland, right?

368
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:16,110
See? Dong Ik seems
to be really enjoying it, too.

369
00:22:19,980 --> 00:22:23,680
I eat out a lot,
so I'm used to more intense flavors.

370
00:22:23,810 --> 00:22:27,080
- It's so good, restaurant-quality.
- I'll be honest.

371
00:22:29,450 --> 00:22:30,790
I think it's delicious, too.

372
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:33,260
It's just so good.

373
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:36,860
Father, you're home.

374
00:22:37,060 --> 00:22:39,430
Father, have a seat.
The food is excellent.

375
00:22:39,530 --> 00:22:41,130
What's a man like him doing
in the kitchen?

376
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,870
Gosh, I knew he'd say
something like that.

377
00:22:44,370 --> 00:22:47,670
Grandfather,
most of the best chefs are men.

378
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:51,810
That stone-age view
isn't just outdated. It's rude.

379
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:52,940
What was that?

380
00:22:53,380 --> 00:22:57,080
Here, try the spicy braised chicken
this man made.

381
00:22:57,380 --> 00:23:01,180
Yes. Come on, Father, have a seat.
It's honestly so good.

382
00:23:01,250 --> 00:23:02,890
No, that's okay.
I don't have an appetite.

383
00:23:02,950 --> 00:23:06,690
Come on. Just have one bite.
Come on, Father.

384
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:14,400
Just try it.

385
00:23:36,990 --> 00:23:38,360
Man, I was so nervous.

386
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:41,730
- What a relief.
- Tell me about it.

387
00:23:42,430 --> 00:23:43,430
Right, honey?

388
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:46,630
Oh, I'm exhausted.

389
00:23:47,530 --> 00:23:48,570
I see.

390
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:51,400
Come to the clinic
the day after tomorrow.

391
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:52,570
We'll take my car.

392
00:23:52,970 --> 00:23:53,970
Okay.

393
00:23:56,170 --> 00:23:59,240
Director Song will be there
to discuss the show's concept.

394
00:23:59,910 --> 00:24:02,580
It's been a while, hasn't it?
Hey, Seong Mi.

395
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:05,150
Rub my feet for me.

396
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:07,150
Are you crazy?

397
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:09,350
What's crazy about
giving your husband a foot massage?

398
00:24:09,420 --> 00:24:12,120
The problem isn't your feet.
It's your attitude.

399
00:24:12,390 --> 00:24:14,790
You've been walking around all day,
you haven't even washed your feet,

400
00:24:14,860 --> 00:24:17,230
and yet you demand I rub them
as if you're entitled to it.

401
00:24:17,460 --> 00:24:20,660
And when I say no, you blame me.
That attitude.

402
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:24,940
That right there is emotional abuse
and gaslighting.

403
00:24:25,070 --> 00:24:27,900
Fine, I guess I am crazy then.
You're right.

404
00:24:28,310 --> 00:24:31,240
Oh, boy. I'll just rub my own feet.

405
00:24:32,840 --> 00:24:35,650
Where are you off to?
Going to sleep in Mom's room again?

406
00:24:35,810 --> 00:24:37,410
I'm sleeping in Ju Ah's room. Why?

407
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:41,790
Come on. We were campaigning today,
holding hands and everything,

408
00:24:41,890 --> 00:24:44,350
with our arms around each other,
so I just thought...

409
00:24:44,750 --> 00:24:46,890
that maybe we could, you know...

410
00:24:47,590 --> 00:24:50,260
I thought we'd be sleeping together.
What? Why? What's with that look?

411
00:24:51,160 --> 00:24:52,960
Don't get the wrong idea.

412
00:24:53,330 --> 00:24:56,430
This is purely a strategic alliance.

413
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:59,700
Once we get paid for the apartment
and your brother's family moves out,

414
00:25:00,100 --> 00:25:01,300
we're sleeping in separate rooms.

415
00:25:02,710 --> 00:25:07,010
I bet Bucket's wife
rubs his feet for him,

416
00:25:07,080 --> 00:25:09,450
and I'm sure they share the same bed
just fine.

417
00:25:09,850 --> 00:25:13,980
- Do you want to die?
- No, forget it. Good night.

418
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:15,790
Oh, boy...

419
00:25:18,790 --> 00:25:20,490
Good grief.

420
00:25:34,070 --> 00:25:36,640
Wait, what are you doing, Doctor?

421
00:25:37,370 --> 00:25:38,810
I'm going to sleep.
Turn off the light.

422
00:25:39,310 --> 00:25:41,810
You moved out of the studio
to stop the rumors.

423
00:25:41,810 --> 00:25:43,910
So, shouldn't you be sharing a room
with your husband?

424
00:25:44,050 --> 00:25:45,880
Quiet. Turn off the light.

425
00:25:45,980 --> 00:25:49,590
Excuse me? Ms. Love Evangelist.
Is your marriage all for show?

426
00:25:49,890 --> 00:25:51,760
Wow, you're such a hypocrite.

427
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:54,320
Hey.

428
00:25:54,660 --> 00:25:57,660
By any chance,
is Woo Jae dating Bucket's daughter?

429
00:25:57,860 --> 00:25:59,400
Gosh, as if.

430
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:02,100
She just has a crush on him
and follows him everywhere.

431
00:26:02,300 --> 00:26:03,530
Even if it were
the greatest romance,

432
00:26:03,530 --> 00:26:04,830
it's absolutely out of the question.

433
00:26:06,170 --> 00:26:08,200
You're sure Woo Jae
isn't interested in her, right?

434
00:26:08,740 --> 00:26:10,570
That's what he said.

435
00:26:10,570 --> 00:26:13,410
But what's with that family?
Are we like a magnet for them?

436
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:16,810
Didn't Dr. Yang
have a thing for you, too?

437
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:20,420
That's not all. Bucket's son
had a crush on you, too.

438
00:26:22,190 --> 00:26:24,990
Wait, you knew about that?

439
00:26:25,590 --> 00:26:26,720
Of course. Did you think I wouldn't?

440
00:26:27,020 --> 00:26:29,490
Your grandma and uncle
may have raised you,

441
00:26:29,490 --> 00:26:33,100
but I'm the one who gave birth
to you and breastfed you.

442
00:26:34,430 --> 00:26:36,430
I might let you get away
with quitting medicine,

443
00:26:36,570 --> 00:26:39,800
but there is no way
you're deciding who you marry.

444
00:26:39,870 --> 00:26:44,170
How did we even get on this topic?
I don't even have a boyfriend, Mom.

445
00:26:44,510 --> 00:26:46,140
My goodness.

446
00:26:46,610 --> 00:26:50,010
Just imagine that woman
as your mother-in-law.

447
00:26:50,210 --> 00:26:52,350
How horrible would that be?

448
00:26:52,750 --> 00:26:56,690
If you analyze her typical behavior,

449
00:26:57,420 --> 00:26:59,860
it's highly likely
she views her son...

450
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:02,930
as a means of
psychological compensation...

451
00:27:03,790 --> 00:27:05,430
Hey, I'm talking here!

452
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:07,700
Just go to sleep, please.

453
00:27:09,330 --> 00:27:11,200
Gosh, this kid.

454
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:18,410
I'm so stuffed. That was delicious.

455
00:27:20,010 --> 00:27:21,480
You liked it that much?

456
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:22,750
I did.

457
00:27:23,250 --> 00:27:26,950
It was the first meal cooked for me
since I married into this family.

458
00:27:28,750 --> 00:27:29,790
No way.

459
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:32,590
Well, I'll cook for you
more often then.

460
00:27:35,290 --> 00:27:37,090
I'm already jealous.

461
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:40,700
The woman who gets to marry my son
is so lucky.

462
00:27:41,770 --> 00:27:46,340
- I don't plan on getting married.
- What? Why not?

463
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:49,040
Is this one of those new trends,
choosing to be single or something?

464
00:27:49,370 --> 00:27:52,680
Marriage isn't just
between two people.

465
00:27:52,780 --> 00:27:55,210
It's about 2 families
becoming 1, you know?

466
00:27:56,780 --> 00:28:01,380
That's not how it is anymore.
All that matters is your happiness.

467
00:28:02,220 --> 00:28:05,320
Our family is honestly embarrassing.
A total embarrassment.

468
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:08,160
Me, too?

469
00:28:09,490 --> 00:28:10,530
Well...

470
00:28:11,330 --> 00:28:14,460
A mother-in-law this young,
pretty, and perfect...

471
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:17,300
It'd probably be a bit intimidating
for the daughter-in-law, right?

472
00:28:21,670 --> 00:28:22,670
I...

473
00:28:23,610 --> 00:28:25,010
I did something terrible, Hyun Bin.

474
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:28,480
You heard from Eun Bin, didn't you?

475
00:28:29,550 --> 00:28:30,550
Yes.

476
00:28:31,150 --> 00:28:33,280
I understand why you did it, but...

477
00:28:34,050 --> 00:28:35,420
you went a little too far.

478
00:28:37,690 --> 00:28:38,690
Fair enough.

479
00:28:40,390 --> 00:28:43,090
But hey, it's not like
Eun Bin is blameless in this either.

480
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:47,160
She's crazy about that guy,
so she ran to tattle to his family.

481
00:28:47,430 --> 00:28:51,470
- She's crazy about some guy?
- Yes. The doctor's son.

482
00:28:51,530 --> 00:28:54,800
It's driving me crazy!
She's completely obsessed with him.

483
00:28:56,370 --> 00:28:59,580
- You don't like that?
- "Don't like" is an understatement.

484
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:03,650
It can never happen.
No, absolutely, never, ever.

485
00:29:13,890 --> 00:29:15,960
Don't tell me
he was your first love, too.

486
00:29:18,900 --> 00:29:22,370
It's already been a year
since you went to study abroad.

487
00:29:23,170 --> 00:29:26,300
You told me not to forget,
but I guess you forgot about me.

488
00:29:26,940 --> 00:29:28,400
I'll be waiting to hear from you.

489
00:29:29,310 --> 00:29:31,840
I miss you, Yang Hyun Bin.

490
00:29:43,590 --> 00:29:46,360
All right, everyone.

491
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:49,760
The vote for the 16th President
of the Merchants' Association...

492
00:29:49,790 --> 00:29:52,400
will now begin.

493
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:54,000
(The 16th Onjeong Market Merchants'
Association Presidential Election)

494
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:55,000
(Number 2, Gong Jeong Han)

495
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:59,140
All right.
Let the candidates vote first.

496
00:29:59,500 --> 00:30:01,070
(Number 2, Gong Jeong Han)

497
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:03,270
(Number 1, Yang Dong Ik)

498
00:30:09,850 --> 00:30:12,820
Only people with a business license
can vote, right?

499
00:30:12,920 --> 00:30:16,520
Yes. We get a vote, and so do they.

500
00:30:20,290 --> 00:30:21,720
Woo Jae.

501
00:30:27,630 --> 00:30:29,200
(Ballot Box)

502
00:30:34,370 --> 00:30:35,770
Get out of the way.

503
00:30:37,140 --> 00:30:38,210
I was here first.

504
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:47,120
Honey.

505
00:30:56,290 --> 00:31:00,560
- This is so embarrassing.
- I wish this were over.

506
00:31:00,630 --> 00:31:01,900
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

507
00:31:02,670 --> 00:31:05,700
Excuse me, who did you vote for?

508
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:10,270
Oh, thank you so much.

509
00:31:12,380 --> 00:31:13,810
That's two votes for us already.

510
00:31:14,010 --> 00:31:16,750
I bet the next person
voted for my brother.

511
00:31:17,850 --> 00:31:18,880
No.

512
00:31:20,420 --> 00:31:21,480
Dad, are you leaving?

513
00:31:25,660 --> 00:31:26,960
Get home safe.

514
00:31:32,100 --> 00:31:33,100
(Yang Dong Ik, Gong Jeong Han)

515
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,730
Gong Jeong Han.

516
00:31:43,610 --> 00:31:45,240
(Number 1 Yang Dong Ik,
Number 2 Gong Jeong Han)

517
00:31:49,710 --> 00:31:51,150
Yang Dong Ik.

518
00:31:55,420 --> 00:31:56,490
Yes!

519
00:32:02,190 --> 00:32:04,460
I don't know why
I'm so nervous about this.

520
00:32:07,660 --> 00:32:10,800
The people who promised us votes.
They came through, right?

521
00:32:10,870 --> 00:32:13,270
Of course. We're going to win.

522
00:32:13,340 --> 00:32:15,570
- Don't you worry, dear.
- Okay.

523
00:32:17,540 --> 00:32:20,110
It's too close to call.

524
00:32:23,150 --> 00:32:24,710
Gong Jeong Han.

525
00:32:26,850 --> 00:32:29,520
- Yang Dong Ik.
- My goodness.

526
00:32:31,750 --> 00:32:32,890
(Yang Dong Ik, Gong Jeong Han)

527
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:36,460
Yang Dong Ik. Gong Jeong Han.

528
00:32:38,860 --> 00:32:42,870
Yang Dong Ik, Gong Jeong Han.
Yang Dong Ik.

529
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:44,870
Gong Jeong Han.

530
00:32:56,910 --> 00:33:00,480
All right,
with both candidates tied,

531
00:33:01,050 --> 00:33:03,190
it all comes down to this last vote.

532
00:33:18,870 --> 00:33:22,040
I will now announce
the results of the 16th...

533
00:33:22,110 --> 00:33:25,310
Merchants' Association
Presidential Election.

534
00:33:27,040 --> 00:33:30,580
Out of the 175 eligible voters,

535
00:33:30,750 --> 00:33:33,880
a total of 167 ballots were cast,

536
00:33:33,980 --> 00:33:36,750
and two were invalid.

537
00:33:37,790 --> 00:33:42,590
Candidate Yang Dong Ik, 82 votes.
Candidate Gong Jeong Han...

538
00:33:42,790 --> 00:33:45,190
received 83 votes.

539
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:48,030
Mr. Gong Jeong Han
has been elected president!

540
00:33:51,470 --> 00:33:52,970
Oh, my!

541
00:33:54,440 --> 00:33:56,710
Mom!

542
00:33:58,340 --> 00:33:59,380
Seong Mi!

543
00:33:59,910 --> 00:34:01,510
Seong Mi, thank you!

544
00:34:08,220 --> 00:34:11,890
The Merchants' Association
Election Committee.

545
00:34:14,590 --> 00:34:15,760
Thank you.

546
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:18,560
Yes.

547
00:34:20,330 --> 00:34:21,730
- Thank you.
- Congratulations.

548
00:34:22,500 --> 00:34:23,800
Thank you.

549
00:34:24,300 --> 00:34:25,300
Thank you.

550
00:34:26,200 --> 00:34:28,570
- Mom!
- Yes.

551
00:34:28,940 --> 00:34:31,670
Come on, get up. Thank you!

552
00:34:32,740 --> 00:34:35,110
Thank you. Thank you so much.

553
00:34:35,180 --> 00:34:38,050
Thank you, everyone. Thank you.

554
00:34:39,450 --> 00:34:41,080
- Thank you.
- Let's go.

555
00:34:41,150 --> 00:34:42,290
I'll work hard for all of you.

556
00:34:42,290 --> 00:34:43,890
- This is amazing.
- Thank you!

557
00:34:43,950 --> 00:34:44,950
Congratulations, really!

558
00:34:52,460 --> 00:34:53,760
You ran a good race.

559
00:35:01,740 --> 00:35:03,540
- Hey, Dong Suk.
- What?

560
00:35:05,740 --> 00:35:08,410
- Seriously, let go!
- Neener!

561
00:35:09,750 --> 00:35:11,850
- You worked so hard!
- You worked hard, too.

562
00:35:11,910 --> 00:35:13,350
- Well done.
- Congratulations!

563
00:35:13,880 --> 00:35:16,090
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much!

564
00:35:16,490 --> 00:35:18,220
You worked hard.

565
00:35:20,220 --> 00:35:21,220
Right.

566
00:35:23,890 --> 00:35:24,890
Well...

567
00:35:25,930 --> 00:35:27,260
Congratulations.

568
00:35:36,970 --> 00:35:41,880
You said you were the bigger person,
but you look like you got revenge.

569
00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:45,050
This isn't revenge.
It's a righteous victory.

570
00:35:45,580 --> 00:35:49,290
- Is it that sweet?
- It's absolutely delicious.

571
00:35:51,150 --> 00:35:53,390
Whatever. Let's go.

572
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:02,060
I'm going to head inside and rest.

573
00:36:05,500 --> 00:36:07,500
After all her big talk...
Unbelievable.

574
00:36:08,100 --> 00:36:09,770
How much money did we waste on this?

575
00:36:10,740 --> 00:36:11,840
What happened?

576
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:14,380
We lost. By a single vote.

577
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:17,610
- One vote?
- Yes. It's so frustrating!

578
00:36:17,810 --> 00:36:20,250
That last vote
should have been ours.

579
00:36:21,250 --> 00:36:24,120
Quick, get me some water.
I need to take my medicine.

580
00:36:26,560 --> 00:36:27,660
Wait a second.

581
00:36:27,990 --> 00:36:30,730
- They counted from the top.
- So what?

582
00:36:31,030 --> 00:36:34,760
So the last vote they counted
was from the first person to vote?

583
00:36:34,930 --> 00:36:38,570
Wait... You and Dad voted first,
didn't you?

584
00:36:38,630 --> 00:36:39,770
You did vote for yourself, right?

585
00:36:39,840 --> 00:36:42,140
Hey, what kind of question is that?
Stop talking nonsense,

586
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:43,510
and go get Dad his water.

587
00:36:43,770 --> 00:36:47,680
That one vote is a shame, isn't it?
You get him the water.

588
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:49,550
The nerve of this girl.

589
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,650
- Hey, you!
- Sorry.

590
00:37:05,090 --> 00:37:06,960
(Always Kind Pharmacy,
Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

591
00:37:14,370 --> 00:37:16,840
Mom, it's cold.
Hey, let's hurry. Okay?

592
00:37:17,410 --> 00:37:19,410
- Yes.
- Oh, hello.

593
00:37:21,740 --> 00:37:26,420
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,
Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

594
00:37:31,520 --> 00:37:33,720
- My goodness! Sir!
- Oh, no!

595
00:37:40,900 --> 00:37:43,530
Gosh, your blood pressure is high.

596
00:37:44,370 --> 00:37:47,500
But at least you're conscious,
and your breathing is stable.

597
00:37:48,270 --> 00:37:51,310
It looks like a blood sugar issue,
so I'll run a blood test first.

598
00:37:51,370 --> 00:37:53,410
- Hey, I'll...
- Yes?

599
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:55,110
- I'll call his family.
- Okay.

600
00:37:55,180 --> 00:37:57,950
No! Don't bother!

601
00:37:58,880 --> 00:38:01,680
I have high blood sugar.

602
00:38:02,050 --> 00:38:04,150
Oh, what about your medication?

603
00:38:04,750 --> 00:38:08,190
- Have you been taking it?
- Yes, after my last check-up,

604
00:38:09,060 --> 00:38:11,030
I just took the one prescription,
and that was it.

605
00:38:11,930 --> 00:38:14,800
Let me start you on an IV
to stabilize your electrolytes.

606
00:38:15,060 --> 00:38:17,970
Mom, please put that big pillow
under his legs.

607
00:38:18,430 --> 00:38:21,500
And I'll write a prescription,
so please get the medicine ready.

608
00:38:21,500 --> 00:38:23,840
- Okay, I got it.
- Yes, just hang on a moment, sir.

609
00:38:27,280 --> 00:38:30,510
(Pharmacy)

610
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:36,150
(Multivitamins)

611
00:38:45,830 --> 00:38:47,160
Please sit up carefully.
There you go.

612
00:38:48,860 --> 00:38:50,730
- Hey, Mom.
- Yes.

613
00:38:52,600 --> 00:38:53,840
Whether I lived or died,

614
00:38:55,710 --> 00:38:57,870
why didn't you just leave me
on the street?

615
00:38:58,410 --> 00:39:01,410
What? Why would I do that?
I'm a doctor.

616
00:39:01,780 --> 00:39:04,250
You must hate the very sight of me.

617
00:39:04,510 --> 00:39:08,580
I see you from my window constantly.
If I hated the sight of you,

618
00:39:08,580 --> 00:39:10,550
I would've moved my clinic
a long time ago.

619
00:39:11,650 --> 00:39:12,660
You must have it tough.

620
00:39:15,220 --> 00:39:16,730
I'm sorry about that.

621
00:39:17,260 --> 00:39:19,130
Sir, why would you say that?

622
00:39:19,960 --> 00:39:22,500
What have you and I ever done wrong?

623
00:39:24,530 --> 00:39:25,530
Here.

624
00:39:26,140 --> 00:39:29,840
Jeong Han's prescription
and your blood sugar supplements.

625
00:39:30,270 --> 00:39:34,980
Don't skip meals. And be careful
with sweets and fruit.

626
00:39:35,780 --> 00:39:39,180
And if I see you buying street food
at the market again,

627
00:39:39,380 --> 00:39:41,020
I'm calling your family.

628
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:42,490
Yes, ma'am.

629
00:39:43,720 --> 00:39:45,190
No matter how old we get,

630
00:39:45,550 --> 00:39:47,690
our children
still need their parents.

631
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:51,730
Isn't that why we've both endured
for so long?

632
00:39:52,660 --> 00:39:55,700
So you have to stay healthy
for a long time.

633
00:39:56,570 --> 00:39:57,570
Right.

634
00:39:57,730 --> 00:40:01,340
I'm open weekend evenings
every other week, so please come by.

635
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:03,410
And if you really
don't want to see me,

636
00:40:03,770 --> 00:40:06,640
at least go to another clinic
to get your prescription filled.

637
00:40:06,940 --> 00:40:09,850
I will be sure to repay you
for saving my life.

638
00:40:10,750 --> 00:40:14,050
What? And how exactly do you plan
on repaying me?

639
00:40:14,550 --> 00:40:15,550
Tomorrow.

640
00:40:16,920 --> 00:40:17,990
I'm going to vote for you.

641
00:40:19,120 --> 00:40:22,460
- Good grief.
- Please, you don't have to.

642
00:40:28,460 --> 00:40:31,000
You'd better know you won
because of me, you punk.

643
00:40:31,930 --> 00:40:33,140
Dad, I'm coming in.

644
00:40:36,670 --> 00:40:37,670
Wait a minute.

645
00:40:38,270 --> 00:40:39,310
What's this medicine you're taking?

646
00:40:40,110 --> 00:40:41,110
They're just vitamins.

647
00:40:43,210 --> 00:40:46,250
We have good herbs at the clinic.
Why would you take vitamins?

648
00:40:47,050 --> 00:40:48,320
It's too much of a hassle
to brew them.

649
00:40:49,220 --> 00:40:52,560
Gosh, losing by one vote...
It's so frustrating, I could die.

650
00:40:52,860 --> 00:40:53,860
What's so frustrating?

651
00:40:54,790 --> 00:40:56,790
He must have been better
than you at something.

652
00:40:57,390 --> 00:40:58,390
Dad, don't tell me...

653
00:40:59,030 --> 00:41:00,560
You didn't vote for Jeong Han,
did you?

654
00:41:02,570 --> 00:41:04,300
- You didn't, right?
- Quiet!

655
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:06,900
Throw all of this out.

656
00:41:07,940 --> 00:41:10,170
What? Seriously?

657
00:41:10,670 --> 00:41:13,640
I told you, but you never listened.
Why the sudden change of heart?

658
00:41:13,880 --> 00:41:15,410
I told you to throw it out,
so just do it!

659
00:41:26,520 --> 00:41:27,790
Jeong Han's father.

660
00:41:29,730 --> 00:41:32,030
Jeong Han has become the president
of the Merchants' Association.

661
00:41:33,200 --> 00:41:34,200
Just like you.

662
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:46,940
He has your warm, considerate heart.

663
00:41:50,480 --> 00:41:53,380
He doesn't say it,
but deep in his heart,

664
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:57,350
I know he resents you,
but also misses you dearly.

665
00:42:03,590 --> 00:42:06,960
Mr. Yang came to see Jeong Han
for treatment.

666
00:42:08,560 --> 00:42:11,330
He's aged so much, just as I have.

667
00:42:15,140 --> 00:42:17,470
As more time passes,
I hope that one day,

668
00:42:18,140 --> 00:42:20,940
the resentment they have
for each other will subside,

669
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:25,410
and these wounded hearts
will finally be able to heal.

670
00:42:36,490 --> 00:42:38,790
(Taehan)

671
00:42:43,830 --> 00:42:45,500
- My gosh!
- The door is now open.

672
00:42:46,970 --> 00:42:48,440
The door is now open.

673
00:42:49,910 --> 00:42:52,470
- Good morning, Ms. Gong.
- Oh, hello...

674
00:42:53,910 --> 00:42:55,440
Did you have a good weekend?

675
00:42:56,550 --> 00:42:57,580
Yes.

676
00:43:02,280 --> 00:43:03,490
My goodness.

677
00:43:20,770 --> 00:43:22,000
A vitamin drink.

678
00:43:22,570 --> 00:43:23,870
I'll bring you one every day.

679
00:43:24,910 --> 00:43:27,640
- Why?
- No reason. I just want to.

680
00:43:40,020 --> 00:43:43,130
What? The Design Office is this way.
Why is she going over there?

681
00:43:43,930 --> 00:43:45,630
- Ms. Gong...
- Hey, don't call her.

682
00:43:46,260 --> 00:43:47,260
Why?

683
00:43:48,230 --> 00:43:49,230
This is going to be interesting.

684
00:43:55,470 --> 00:43:58,810
We only spent a few days together.
Why do I feel so empty?

685
00:43:58,970 --> 00:44:00,910
(Executive Director
Pacundo Ignacio de la Cruz Yang)

686
00:44:03,610 --> 00:44:04,850
Good morning.

687
00:44:05,810 --> 00:44:08,250
(Taehan Group)

688
00:44:10,150 --> 00:44:11,150
Let's see.

689
00:44:12,420 --> 00:44:14,990
Great, now I'm seeing things.

690
00:44:15,660 --> 00:44:18,060
Gong Ju Ah is back
in the Design Office.

691
00:44:18,460 --> 00:44:19,660
There's no way she'd be here.

692
00:44:21,860 --> 00:44:22,870
Right!

693
00:44:24,630 --> 00:44:25,970
Why am I here?

694
00:44:26,470 --> 00:44:27,470
Excuse me?

695
00:44:30,210 --> 00:44:31,540
Gosh, where is my head?

696
00:44:32,470 --> 00:44:34,680
I'm so sorry. Excuse me.

697
00:44:35,510 --> 00:44:37,250
Wait, Ms. Gong.

698
00:44:37,850 --> 00:44:38,980
Please don't make fun of me.

699
00:44:39,750 --> 00:44:41,580
This is embarrassing enough already.

700
00:44:44,720 --> 00:44:46,060
No, it's not that.

701
00:44:47,790 --> 00:44:51,230
I wanted to say I had a great time
with my family, thanks to you.

702
00:44:52,330 --> 00:44:54,130
Okay. Yes.

703
00:44:54,900 --> 00:44:55,900
I'm glad to hear that.

704
00:44:56,900 --> 00:44:57,900
I'll be going.

705
00:45:14,850 --> 00:45:19,050
You jerk! Why didn't you tell me?
I made a complete fool of myself!

706
00:45:19,290 --> 00:45:23,290
Don't blame me. It was your instinct
pulling you toward him.

707
00:45:23,360 --> 00:45:25,290
Seriously, shut it.

708
00:45:33,370 --> 00:45:35,270
- Ms. Kim?
- Yes.

709
00:45:35,270 --> 00:45:37,070
I'll attend
the Design Team's workshop as well.

710
00:45:37,740 --> 00:45:39,680
Postpone any meetings I have
and clear my schedule.

711
00:45:40,110 --> 00:45:41,110
Understood.

712
00:45:48,720 --> 00:45:50,420
You're packing already?
We haven't even found a new place.

713
00:45:50,890 --> 00:45:54,320
Yes. Seong Mi said she's getting
the final payment tomorrow,

714
00:45:54,390 --> 00:45:55,390
so we need to be ready.

715
00:45:56,790 --> 00:45:58,460
- Honey, come sit down.
- What?

716
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:04,500
Once we move, let's invite the aunt
who raised you to come visit.

717
00:46:05,500 --> 00:46:08,700
No, forget it. If I see her,
we'll just end up fighting.

718
00:46:09,300 --> 00:46:12,440
She tried marrying me
to a rich old man for a quick buck,

719
00:46:12,610 --> 00:46:16,450
so she's still fuming
that I ran away and ruined her plan.

720
00:46:17,880 --> 00:46:20,980
Still, I'm actually grateful
to that man and your aunt.

721
00:46:21,480 --> 00:46:22,720
Thanks to them,

722
00:46:23,150 --> 00:46:24,920
you found your way
to Onjeong and met me.

723
00:46:26,690 --> 00:46:28,120
Dae Han, let's go.

724
00:46:28,490 --> 00:46:30,130
Okay, I'll be right out.

725
00:46:30,860 --> 00:46:32,590
Honey, things are
about to get even busier for me.

726
00:46:33,000 --> 00:46:34,000
See you later.

727
00:46:39,670 --> 00:46:41,270
- I'm heading out.
- Okay.

728
00:46:42,240 --> 00:46:43,240
Jeong Han!

729
00:46:44,670 --> 00:46:48,040
All right, let's begin
the Onjeong Market warm-up!

730
00:46:48,140 --> 00:46:51,180
One, two, three, four,

731
00:46:51,510 --> 00:46:54,050
five, six, seven, eight.

732
00:46:54,380 --> 00:46:57,020
Two, two, three, four,

733
00:46:57,290 --> 00:47:00,060
five, six, seven, eight.

734
00:47:00,190 --> 00:47:03,930
Make a nice heart over your head.
That's it.

735
00:47:03,990 --> 00:47:04,990
Now, to the left.

736
00:47:05,330 --> 00:47:07,900
- One, two, three, four.
- One, two, three, four.

737
00:47:08,160 --> 00:47:13,070
We love Onjeong Market!
Two, two, three, four.

738
00:47:13,470 --> 00:47:16,410
- Let's make it big, Onjeong Market!
- Let's make it big, Onjeong Market!

739
00:47:16,510 --> 00:47:20,680
- Okay. Face the front again.
- Gosh, the noise is killing me.

740
00:47:21,180 --> 00:47:23,650
He's making such a scene,
acting like a complete fool.

741
00:47:24,480 --> 00:47:27,220
Is he really doing this every day?
For the next three years?

742
00:47:27,750 --> 00:47:28,950
It was one of his campaign pledges.

743
00:47:29,380 --> 00:47:32,290
- If he says he'll do it, he will.
- Oh, gosh.

744
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:36,120
So is your shot
at the City Council over then?

745
00:47:36,560 --> 00:47:37,790
Didn't you have to
become president...

746
00:47:37,790 --> 00:47:39,390
of the Merchants' Association
to be nominated?

747
00:47:39,660 --> 00:47:41,700
Your sister-in-law is taking care
of everything.

748
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:45,070
- So what's her plan now?
- Onjeong Market!

749
00:47:46,000 --> 00:47:47,900
Here. This is for you.

750
00:47:49,100 --> 00:47:52,240
The moment I saw this scarf
at the department store,

751
00:47:52,770 --> 00:47:57,150
I just knew it would be
the perfect color on you.

752
00:47:58,210 --> 00:48:00,850
Sweetie, you must've heard
that my husband and I...

753
00:48:01,280 --> 00:48:03,020
are getting together for golf
with Mr. Hwang and his wife.

754
00:48:05,190 --> 00:48:07,790
If you could just arrange
for us to meet,

755
00:48:08,290 --> 00:48:11,160
I'll make it well worth your while.

756
00:48:11,730 --> 00:48:13,730
I heard he lost
the Merchants' Association election.

757
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:15,900
Bringing up the nomination
in this situation...

758
00:48:16,500 --> 00:48:18,500
would put Mr. Hwang
in an awkward spot.

759
00:48:18,970 --> 00:48:21,300
Appearances and justification
are very important to him.

760
00:48:22,640 --> 00:48:24,610
It was only by a single vote,
you know.

761
00:48:25,010 --> 00:48:29,710
With a small margin, we can turn
opinion before the nomination.

762
00:48:31,480 --> 00:48:34,080
Well, I feel bad taking this
for nothing.

763
00:48:35,420 --> 00:48:37,120
So how about
I give you a little tip?

764
00:48:39,120 --> 00:48:40,120
A tip?

765
00:48:41,420 --> 00:48:43,830
I wonder what she wants today.

766
00:48:44,160 --> 00:48:48,760
I let my family brand me as disloyal
to save your mother...

767
00:48:48,860 --> 00:48:52,600
and helped your dad win his race.
You can't just let that slide.

768
00:48:52,770 --> 00:48:56,440
Your dad only won the election
because of my noble sacrifice.

769
00:48:56,570 --> 00:48:59,370
- Right?
- Sure, let's go with that.

770
00:48:59,810 --> 00:49:00,810
Thanks.

771
00:49:01,040 --> 00:49:05,680
Grant me one wish. If you refuse,
I'll show up every single day.

772
00:49:06,210 --> 00:49:07,220
What's your wish?

773
00:49:08,350 --> 00:49:09,520
Go on a date with me.

774
00:49:09,920 --> 00:49:12,720
We can wear matching outfits,
eat malatang,

775
00:49:12,790 --> 00:49:16,790
see a movie, take some photos,
and go to a cafe for dessert.

776
00:49:16,890 --> 00:49:18,390
And I refuse to take no
for an answer.

777
00:49:20,260 --> 00:49:21,700
Fine. Let's do it.

778
00:49:23,070 --> 00:49:27,000
- Really?
- But we can't tell our families.

779
00:49:27,070 --> 00:49:28,240
Got it.

780
00:49:28,870 --> 00:49:29,870
Promise!

781
00:49:32,140 --> 00:49:33,140
Promise.

782
00:49:33,680 --> 00:49:35,010
I'm so happy.

783
00:49:38,610 --> 00:49:40,450
So when are we doing this?

784
00:49:45,350 --> 00:49:48,020
Are you sure it's okay for me
to get free food like this so often?

785
00:49:48,060 --> 00:49:51,890
It's fine. They're not from me.
They're gifts from our patients.

786
00:49:52,260 --> 00:49:53,400
I see.

787
00:49:54,060 --> 00:49:56,060
So why are you eating here today?

788
00:49:56,970 --> 00:49:59,770
Dr. Gong has a meeting
with the Merchants' Association.

789
00:49:59,870 --> 00:50:02,170
Ms. Na went to view the new house
Mr. Gong is moving into.

790
00:50:02,870 --> 00:50:03,870
I see.

791
00:50:05,270 --> 00:50:06,940
So Mr. Gong is moving.

792
00:50:07,210 --> 00:50:09,780
Yes, they've been married
for five years and are moving out.

793
00:50:11,080 --> 00:50:14,720
They're already such a great couple.
They'll get even closer now.

794
00:50:14,850 --> 00:50:16,180
I know, right?

795
00:50:16,180 --> 00:50:19,550
Clinic manager and his wife,
married for five years.

796
00:50:19,890 --> 00:50:22,520
A happy couple,
planning to move out.

797
00:50:23,460 --> 00:50:24,830
You really write down everything,
don't you?

798
00:50:24,990 --> 00:50:27,130
I bet he wrote about you
in there too, Nurse Oh.

799
00:50:27,400 --> 00:50:29,130
- Me?
- Yes.

800
00:50:30,630 --> 00:50:32,200
- What does it say?
- Hey! You can't see.

801
00:50:32,500 --> 00:50:34,070
- Why not?
- No way!

802
00:50:34,140 --> 00:50:35,940
I have a right to see
what you wrote. Right, Chief?

803
00:50:36,000 --> 00:50:39,270
- Sir, that's classified.
- Come on! Isn't this illegal?

804
00:50:39,410 --> 00:50:41,180
- That was close.
- It's classified.

805
00:50:41,240 --> 00:50:42,240
- Eat up.
- Come on.

806
00:50:45,210 --> 00:50:48,020
- Please, feel free to look around.
- Okay.

807
00:50:50,990 --> 00:50:53,660
- The balcony is so spacious.
- Yes, it is.

808
00:50:55,190 --> 00:50:57,630
- So, this is the master bedroom?
- Yes, that's right.

809
00:50:58,990 --> 00:51:03,130
The layout is so good,
it looks more spacious than it is.

810
00:51:04,130 --> 00:51:06,540
You certainly have a good eye,
ma'am.

811
00:51:06,800 --> 00:51:09,700
This unit is south-facing,
so it gets plenty of sunlight.

812
00:51:09,870 --> 00:51:13,210
Mom, the hot water works great,
and the pressure is strong, too.

813
00:51:14,410 --> 00:51:17,410
But shouldn't Hui Gyeong be the one
to see it and decide?

814
00:51:18,080 --> 00:51:19,150
Don't worry about Hui Gyeong.

815
00:51:19,480 --> 00:51:21,320
She said she'll love
anything you pick out, Mom.

816
00:51:21,980 --> 00:51:24,650
Goodness. Aren't you just excited
to be living alone with her?

817
00:51:25,050 --> 00:51:26,050
You think so?

818
00:51:27,020 --> 00:51:28,020
I guess that must be it.

819
00:51:29,060 --> 00:51:31,530
The place is vacant,

820
00:51:31,760 --> 00:51:35,030
- so can they move in anytime?
- Absolutely.

821
00:51:35,430 --> 00:51:37,030
Let's go sign the contract,
shall we?

822
00:51:37,330 --> 00:51:38,470
Okay. Sure.

823
00:51:39,300 --> 00:51:40,300
Come, this way.

824
00:51:45,270 --> 00:51:49,440
(3H Acupressure Bed)

825
00:51:50,180 --> 00:51:52,210
- Welcome.
- Hi.

826
00:51:53,350 --> 00:51:55,250
Mom, what's this?
Are you buying something?

827
00:51:55,680 --> 00:51:59,050
Since you're moving,
let's get you a new bed. My treat.

828
00:52:05,390 --> 00:52:09,160
- This is nice and warm.
- Mom, come on, you don't have to.

829
00:52:09,600 --> 00:52:11,300
The one we have is
still perfectly fine.

830
00:52:11,900 --> 00:52:14,040
You're moving into a new home,
so you should have new furniture.

831
00:52:14,500 --> 00:52:16,200
You'll feel like newlyweds again,
right?

832
00:52:19,840 --> 00:52:20,840
(3H Acupressure Bed)

833
00:52:23,750 --> 00:52:26,650
Yes. It honestly feels like a dream.

834
00:52:27,050 --> 00:52:31,290
I'm just so happy our wish came true
sooner than we thought, darling.

835
00:52:33,120 --> 00:52:34,120
My husband?

836
00:52:35,460 --> 00:52:37,030
Of course, he has no idea.

837
00:52:37,790 --> 00:52:41,500
Okay, I get it.
Then I'll see you tomorrow, darling.

838
00:52:41,860 --> 00:52:42,860
Bye!

839
00:52:50,270 --> 00:52:54,580
- You scared me! What do you want?
- Is that how you greet a customer?

840
00:52:56,550 --> 00:52:59,250
I'm so sorry.
You just really startled me.

841
00:52:59,810 --> 00:53:01,350
But I can't do your hair right now.

842
00:53:01,680 --> 00:53:04,490
It's lunchtime.
The salon owner is out for a meal.

843
00:53:04,550 --> 00:53:06,960
Could you come back later,
or would you like to wait?

844
00:53:19,970 --> 00:53:22,300
I'm pretty sure
she's having an affair.

845
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:25,270
She was all,
"honey" this and "darling" that.

846
00:53:27,640 --> 00:53:30,110
Should I tell Gong Dae Han
about this?

847
00:53:33,550 --> 00:53:35,350
Shoot, I don't have his number.

848
00:53:36,420 --> 00:53:38,550
Forget it.
It's none of my business anyway.

849
00:53:39,050 --> 00:53:40,390
Let her do what she wants.

850
00:53:42,360 --> 00:53:44,230
Are we still on
for the workshop tomorrow?

851
00:53:45,790 --> 00:53:49,360
This isn't for the whole division.
Only the Design Team is going.

852
00:53:49,660 --> 00:53:51,570
Oh, that's awesome.

853
00:53:52,670 --> 00:53:55,040
I've planned the itinerary,
so just bring what you need.

854
00:53:58,240 --> 00:54:00,010
Excuse me, I have to take this.
It's the Vice President.

855
00:54:01,510 --> 00:54:02,610
Yes, Vice President.

856
00:54:03,380 --> 00:54:04,380
Yes.

857
00:54:07,350 --> 00:54:09,480
What? Why would the Vice President
go to the workshop?

858
00:54:17,990 --> 00:54:20,760
Okay, I'll call you right back. Yes.

859
00:54:20,930 --> 00:54:23,000
Don't hang up. I'm going, too.

860
00:54:25,330 --> 00:54:27,770
I'm afraid you can't.

861
00:54:28,200 --> 00:54:29,440
I'm the Vice President.

862
00:54:34,840 --> 00:54:35,910
Unbelievable.

863
00:54:38,650 --> 00:54:41,280
Yes. Where was I?

864
00:54:42,120 --> 00:54:43,120
You were telling us what to bring.

865
00:54:43,250 --> 00:54:46,920
Right. The first piece
each of you ever created.

866
00:54:46,990 --> 00:54:47,990
That's what you need to bring.

867
00:54:48,420 --> 00:54:50,060
Let's call it...

868
00:54:51,060 --> 00:54:52,430
"My First Creation."

869
00:54:53,900 --> 00:54:54,900
Creation?

870
00:54:56,730 --> 00:54:58,330
My First Creation...

871
00:55:00,900 --> 00:55:01,900
A tip? What do you mean?

872
00:55:02,570 --> 00:55:03,570
What tip?

873
00:55:03,870 --> 00:55:05,810
If you can't get the gold,
you go for the silver.

874
00:55:06,880 --> 00:55:10,110
- What, are we in the Finals?
- Oh, come on!

875
00:55:10,810 --> 00:55:15,320
If you can't be the president,
let's at least secure the VP spot.

876
00:55:16,320 --> 00:55:17,320
Vice President?

877
00:55:17,390 --> 00:55:20,760
To the public, there's no difference
if you're president or VP.

878
00:55:21,020 --> 00:55:22,560
You're still an executive
of the Merchants' Association.

879
00:55:22,960 --> 00:55:24,830
That's the one line you need
on your resume.

880
00:55:26,030 --> 00:55:27,030
It's not like...

881
00:55:27,930 --> 00:55:29,630
I can get it just by wanting it.

882
00:55:30,570 --> 00:55:31,900
It's an elected position.

883
00:55:32,470 --> 00:55:33,540
So you'll have to go to Dr. Gong...

884
00:55:33,940 --> 00:55:36,640
and ask him nicely. Right, honey?

885
00:55:39,510 --> 00:55:42,110
No way. I'm not doing it.
I have my pride.

886
00:55:43,650 --> 00:55:44,780
Is that so?

887
00:55:45,280 --> 00:55:47,880
Fine, honey.
Shall I go and ask him, then?

888
00:55:47,980 --> 00:55:50,490
I'd do anything for you.

889
00:55:52,520 --> 00:55:53,520
Don't.

890
00:55:54,290 --> 00:55:55,360
I'll do it.

891
00:55:56,690 --> 00:55:57,960
Okay, then.

892
00:56:02,960 --> 00:56:04,270
Hang on.

893
00:56:04,270 --> 00:56:06,570
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

894
00:56:17,410 --> 00:56:19,010
Hey, you really scared me.

895
00:56:19,550 --> 00:56:20,780
What is it?

896
00:56:21,180 --> 00:56:23,080
- Are you busy?
- Yes, I am.

897
00:56:23,220 --> 00:56:24,850
- Well...
- Yang Dong Ik?

898
00:56:26,550 --> 00:56:28,520
Director Song, come out.
Bucket is here.

899
00:56:29,620 --> 00:56:31,890
Hey, Bucket. It's me, Song Jae Geun.

900
00:56:32,160 --> 00:56:33,930
- Long time no see.
- What?

901
00:56:34,800 --> 00:56:35,800
Yes.

902
00:56:35,860 --> 00:56:38,630
We're in a meeting for our show.
What do you want?

903
00:56:39,200 --> 00:56:40,900
No, it's nothing.

904
00:56:41,900 --> 00:56:42,900
Hey.

905
00:56:43,170 --> 00:56:46,640
Is it true your wife took pictures
of Seong Mi and me...

906
00:56:46,710 --> 00:56:48,110
and spread a rumor of an affair
to get you elected?

907
00:56:48,480 --> 00:56:49,480
What?

908
00:56:56,250 --> 00:56:58,420
What is it? Say something, man.

909
00:57:01,190 --> 00:57:03,420
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

910
00:57:03,490 --> 00:57:04,860
What's with him?

911
00:57:06,130 --> 00:57:08,300
I don't know. But...

912
00:57:08,800 --> 00:57:10,030
something's definitely not right.

913
00:57:11,170 --> 00:57:12,170
Goodness.

914
00:57:13,670 --> 00:57:15,200
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

915
00:57:17,610 --> 00:57:18,610
Oh, my.

916
00:57:19,270 --> 00:57:20,780
Is it all sorted out already?

917
00:57:25,010 --> 00:57:26,010
I'm not doing it.

918
00:57:26,580 --> 00:57:29,250
Why not? Why? Did he say no?

919
00:57:33,150 --> 00:57:35,320
What happened, honey? Wait, honey!

920
00:57:35,390 --> 00:57:36,490
(Onjeong Traditional Market)

921
00:57:37,530 --> 00:57:39,060
(H and J)

922
00:57:41,900 --> 00:57:44,830
Long time no see, my first creation.

923
00:57:44,900 --> 00:57:46,670
(H and J)

924
00:57:49,070 --> 00:57:51,540
But should I really bring this?

925
00:57:55,540 --> 00:57:57,950
Hey, Ju Ah. Jokbal and beer.

926
00:57:58,710 --> 00:58:00,280
- Deal!
- Deal!

927
00:58:02,780 --> 00:58:04,520
- All right.
- Cheers!

928
00:58:08,890 --> 00:58:09,890
This is delicious.

929
00:58:10,260 --> 00:58:13,060
Uncle, once you move,
we won't do this often, will we?

930
00:58:13,230 --> 00:58:15,130
What are you talking about?
My new place is around the corner.

931
00:58:15,500 --> 00:58:17,070
I have to come see my favorite kids
all the time.

932
00:58:18,400 --> 00:58:21,500
Even after I move,
call me whenever you want to chat.

933
00:58:22,470 --> 00:58:23,670
Actually,
I have something to tell you guys.

934
00:58:25,940 --> 00:58:28,810
You know, Yang Hyun Bin
from Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic.

935
00:58:28,810 --> 00:58:30,710
- He's back.
- What?

936
00:58:32,110 --> 00:58:34,220
You mean that snot-nosed kid
who had a crush on you?

937
00:58:35,480 --> 00:58:38,150
Yes. And get this,
that same Yang Hyun Bin...

938
00:58:38,650 --> 00:58:40,050
is a director at my company now.

939
00:58:40,150 --> 00:58:43,990
A director? The guy
who moved into Mom's studio...

940
00:58:44,060 --> 00:58:45,860
- is Eun Bin's brother?
- Yes.

941
00:58:45,860 --> 00:58:49,430
Anyway,
we're weirdly tied to that family.

942
00:58:49,430 --> 00:58:50,700
What rotten luck.

943
00:58:51,730 --> 00:58:55,000
Maybe that's why he acts
like he doesn't know me.

944
00:58:55,240 --> 00:58:56,300
Really?

945
00:58:56,370 --> 00:58:59,470
Why? Is he embarrassed
by his old crush?

946
00:59:00,210 --> 00:59:03,440
He's afraid his family will find out
and act like you are now.

947
00:59:03,950 --> 00:59:07,380
I guess Mom will see him tomorrow
for the final payment.

948
00:59:07,650 --> 00:59:10,950
Who even pays in person these days?
You just wire the money.

949
00:59:11,020 --> 00:59:12,020
Goodness.

950
00:59:13,050 --> 00:59:14,920
Yes, I have the final payment ready,
all in cash.

951
00:59:15,290 --> 00:59:17,460
Okay,
I'll go to the realtor's as planned.

952
00:59:18,830 --> 00:59:19,930
Where are you off to?

953
00:59:20,730 --> 00:59:22,700
I need to make the final payment
on Hyun Bin's studio apartment.

954
00:59:23,900 --> 00:59:26,030
But what should I do about this?
The timing is a little...

955
00:59:26,430 --> 00:59:28,170
What's wrong? What's that?

956
00:59:28,770 --> 00:59:32,440
It's a rented bag and accessories.
The rental shop was to pick them up,

957
00:59:32,510 --> 00:59:34,510
but the timing is a little tight.

958
00:59:36,010 --> 00:59:39,750
Leave them. I'm leaving later,
so I'll make sure they get them.

959
00:59:40,450 --> 00:59:43,480
Really? Would you?
Thank you, Yong Gil.

960
00:59:45,490 --> 00:59:47,360
This is quite a surprise.

961
00:59:48,560 --> 00:59:51,190
I know, right? I wondered
who demands the final amount...

962
00:59:51,260 --> 00:59:52,930
in cash these days,

963
00:59:54,860 --> 00:59:56,130
and it turned out to be you, Doctor.

964
00:59:56,560 --> 00:59:57,930
I have my reasons.

965
00:59:59,070 --> 01:00:03,100
It's a small world, isn't it?
I used to live there.

966
01:00:03,170 --> 01:00:04,970
I never thought your son would be
the one to move in.

967
01:00:06,140 --> 01:00:08,310
My son's company is nearby.

968
01:00:09,240 --> 01:00:11,050
You've heard of Taehan Group,
haven't you?

969
01:00:11,650 --> 01:00:12,810
He's a director there.

970
01:00:13,510 --> 01:00:14,550
Taehan?

971
01:00:15,520 --> 01:00:18,050
My daughter works at Taehan, too.
She's a designer.

972
01:00:24,030 --> 01:00:27,760
You see, a rank-and-file employee...

973
01:00:28,230 --> 01:00:32,000
and a corporate executive are
on completely different levels.

974
01:00:33,670 --> 01:00:36,270
You seem to feel better when
you put everyone into hierarchies.

975
01:00:36,400 --> 01:00:39,110
That must be an occupational hazard
for you, Doctor.

976
01:00:39,370 --> 01:00:41,940
Carelessly analyzing everyone
you meet.

977
01:00:42,010 --> 01:00:46,610
If you're offended by my analysis,
it just means I've hit a nerve.

978
01:01:05,900 --> 01:01:06,930
Why are you...

979
01:01:13,780 --> 01:01:14,910
I'm sorry, Director.

980
01:01:15,240 --> 01:01:18,550
For some reason, I get carsick
if I sit in the front seat.

981
01:01:18,810 --> 01:01:19,980
Don't worry.

982
01:01:20,480 --> 01:01:22,820
I was planning on driving anyway.

983
01:01:23,150 --> 01:01:26,620
I have no intention of telling you
the destination beforehand.

984
01:01:27,620 --> 01:01:28,760
But, Director...

985
01:01:29,190 --> 01:01:31,990
Where could we possibly be going
that requires this much secrecy?

986
01:01:34,130 --> 01:01:36,760
You'll just have to wonder.

987
01:01:37,670 --> 01:01:40,200
I heard the HR Team's workshop
was at a five-star hotel.

988
01:01:40,640 --> 01:01:41,970
So we're going there too, right?

989
01:01:43,300 --> 01:01:46,610
Whatever you're imagining,
it'll be better than that.

990
01:01:49,910 --> 01:01:53,850
- Five-star.
- Five-star.

991
01:01:53,980 --> 01:01:55,220
- Five-star.
- Five-star.

992
01:01:55,780 --> 01:01:57,820
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

993
01:01:58,690 --> 01:02:01,860
I would've brought it after work.
Why did you come all this way?

994
01:02:02,120 --> 01:02:04,060
I couldn't wait another second.

995
01:02:07,060 --> 01:02:08,060
This is amazing.

996
01:02:09,060 --> 01:02:12,730
- You're that happy?
- Yes. When I think of the future,

997
01:02:12,800 --> 01:02:14,170
I'm just so happy.

998
01:02:15,900 --> 01:02:17,270
I'm sorry for everything.

999
01:02:17,770 --> 01:02:20,040
It must have been hard on you,
living together because of me.

1000
01:02:20,980 --> 01:02:24,780
That's all in the past now.
I'm truly grateful to you.

1001
01:02:25,810 --> 01:02:27,150
How about we grab lunch together
before you go?

1002
01:02:27,420 --> 01:02:30,850
No, I should go.
Someone's waiting for me. Bye.

1003
01:02:31,550 --> 01:02:33,350
- Okay, see you later.
- Okay.

1004
01:02:34,790 --> 01:02:38,160
What do you mean our house deposit
hasn't come through?

1005
01:02:39,060 --> 01:02:43,130
My daughter-in-law was supposed
to drop it off last night.

1006
01:02:43,800 --> 01:02:47,370
Hey, beautiful.
Did she give you the last payment?

1007
01:02:48,740 --> 01:02:51,440
Why did you ask for it in cash?
It's so bulky and risky.

1008
01:02:52,070 --> 01:02:53,170
Hurry home, and be careful.

1009
01:02:53,540 --> 01:02:56,640
Honey. I'm not coming back.

1010
01:02:57,280 --> 01:02:59,150
I called to tell you
that I'm leaving you.

1011
01:03:01,180 --> 01:03:03,220
What? What are you talking about?

1012
01:03:03,680 --> 01:03:05,020
What do you mean
you're not coming back?

1013
01:03:06,020 --> 01:03:07,050
Look, honey.

1014
01:03:08,060 --> 01:03:09,190
Leaving? Where are you going?

1015
01:03:15,900 --> 01:03:19,070
Please try to understand, honey.

1016
01:03:20,030 --> 01:03:22,070
Of course, I understand, honey.
I always do.

1017
01:03:23,440 --> 01:03:24,940
Thank you for understanding.

1018
01:03:25,440 --> 01:03:28,110
In that case,
I guess this is goodbye.

1019
01:03:28,710 --> 01:03:29,840
Bye.

1020
01:03:30,480 --> 01:03:31,480
Hello?

1021
01:03:32,710 --> 01:03:33,750
Hello? Honey?

1022
01:03:35,180 --> 01:03:36,220
Was that Hui Gyeong?

1023
01:03:39,490 --> 01:03:40,490
Mom.

1024
01:03:41,120 --> 01:03:42,220
What did she say?

1025
01:03:43,290 --> 01:03:46,160
- What?
- What did she say?

1026
01:04:16,120 --> 01:04:18,930
(Recipe For Love)

1027
01:04:18,990 --> 01:04:21,400
I'll have to get on my knees and beg
to be Vice President.

1028
01:04:21,460 --> 01:04:22,800
There's a way
to get the same result...

1029
01:04:22,800 --> 01:04:26,070
without actually having to do it.
I'll show you how.

1030
01:04:26,530 --> 01:04:30,140
This has Bucket's wife's
fingerprints all over it.

1031
01:04:30,370 --> 01:04:32,870
I've made thorough preparations,
so there's no need to worry.

1032
01:04:32,870 --> 01:04:36,280
How dare you call his father a thief
when you don't even know the facts?

1033
01:04:36,340 --> 01:04:39,050
If he's caused trouble again,
I'm kicking you all out this time.

1034
01:04:40,920 --> 01:04:43,350
- It's romantic.
- I knew it.

1035
01:04:43,420 --> 01:04:47,320
You're talking to me
like you knew me in the past.

1036
01:04:48,060 --> 01:04:51,360
I need you to run a location trace.
Please, you have to help me.

1037
01:04:53,660 --> 01:04:54,660
Ganghwa?
